# Add more specific product model types (though noria:ProductModel is a class, not a property)
# This is implicitly handled by the rdfs:label and rdfs:comment of the ProductModel instances.

# Ensure all entities are connected and dense.
# The current structure ensures this by linking resources to locations, products, and managers;
# applications to modules; modules to applications and teams; services to applications/resources;
# trouble tickets to services/applications/resources, events, and parties;
# change requests to impacted elements and parties;
# events to originating objects and systems;
# notes to tickets and authors;
# attachments to tickets/CRs;
# and procedural elements to each other.
# The use of sub-properties like noria:eventRelatedElement and noria:elementManagedBy also helps.
